{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GrGbYLkNrSmfD3qp1r5c9v","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 9-3: Init orchestrator per-stack iteration\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer running `codeharness init` on a multi-stack project,\n     8→I want coverage and OTLP to be configured for each detected stack,\n     9→So that all languages get observability and test coverage.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given a multi-stack project (nodejs + rust), when `codeharness init` runs, then coverage tools are detected for each stack independently (c8 for nodejs, cargo-tarpaulin for rust) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given a multi-stack project (nodejs + rust), when `codeharness init` runs, then OTLP packages are installed for each stack independently (npm packages for nodejs, cargo crates for rust) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given a multi-stack project, when `codeharness init` runs, then info messages list all detected stacks (e.g., `Stack detected: Node.js (package.json) + Rust (Cargo.toml)`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC4: Given a multi-stack project, when state is created, then `state.stacks` contains all detected stack names and `state.app_type` reflects primary stack <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→\n    18→## Technical Notes\n    19→\n    20→### Changes to `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts`\n    21→\n    22→This is the main orchestration change. The `initProjectInner()` function (L51-162) currently calls `detectStack()` at L68 and uses the single result throughout.\n    23→\n    24→**Replace at L68:**\n    25→```ts\n    26→// OLD\n    27→const stack = detectStack(projectDir);\n    28→// NEW\n    29→const detections = detectStacks(projectDir);\n    30→const stacks = detections.map(d => d.stack);\n    31→const primaryStack = stacks[0] ?? null;\n    32→```\n    33→\n    34→**Per-stack iteration for coverage (around L90-100):**\n    35→```ts\n    36→// OLD: single detectCoverageTool(projectDir) call\n    37→// NEW: iterate over detections\n    38→for (const detection of detections) {\n    39→  const stackDir = detection.dir === '.' ? projectDir : path.join(projectDir, detection.dir);\n    40→  const coverageTool = detectCoverageTool(stackDir);\n    41→  // store per-stack coverage result\n    42→}\n    43→```\n    44→\n    45→**Per-stack iteration for OTLP (around L110-130):**\n    46→```ts\n    47→// OLD: single instrumentProject(projectDir, stack) call\n    48→// NEW: iterate over detections\n    49→for (const detection of detections) {\n    50→  const stackDir = detection.dir === '.' ? projectDir : path.join(projectDir, detection.dir);\n    51→  await instrumentProject(stackDir, detection.stack);\n    52→}\n    53→```\n    54→\n    55→**Per-stack app type detection:**\n    56→Call `detectAppType()` for each stack independently. Store `app_types: Record<string, AppType>` in state. Primary `app_type` = `stacks[0]`'s type.\n    57→\n    58→**State creation update:**\n    59→```ts\n    60→state.stacks = stacks;\n    61→state.stack = primaryStack; // compat\n    62→state.app_type = primaryAppType;\n    63→```\n    64→\n    65→**Info messages:**\n    66→Log all detected stacks: `Stack detected: Node.js (package.json) + Rust (Cargo.toml)` using `getStackLabel(stacks)` from docs-scaffold.\n    67→\n    68→### Important: coverage.ts and otlp.ts internals do NOT change\n    69→\n    70→`detectCoverageTool()` (L35-53 in coverage.ts) and `instrumentProject()` (L345 in otlp.ts) keep their single-stack signatures. The orchestrator loops — the internals don't know about multi-stack. This is the minimal API surface change strategy from the tech spec.\n    71→\n    72→### Import changes\n    73→\n    74→Add import of `detectStacks` and `StackDetection` from `../lib/stack-detect`. Keep `detectStack` import if still used elsewhere in the file.\n    75→\n    76→### Test file\n    77→\n    78→Update `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts`:\n    79→- Mock `detectStacks()` to return multi-stack result\n    80→- Verify `detectCoverageTool()` called once per stack\n    81→- Verify `instrumentProject()` called once per stack with correct dir\n    82→- Verify state has `stacks: ['nodejs', 'rust']`\n    83→- Verify single-stack still works (backward compat)\n    84→\n    85→## Files to Change\n    86→\n    87→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — Replace `detectStack()` call at L68 with `detectStacks()`, add per-stack iteration loops for coverage detection and OTLP instrumentation, update state creation to set `stacks[]`, update info messages\n    88→- `src/commands/init.ts` — Update if it references `stack` from `InitResult` (change to `stacks`)\n    89→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts` — Add multi-stack orchestration tests (per-stack coverage, per-stack OTLP, state fields, info messages)\n    90→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NquLEscKgNYqRefYHqoXxE","session_id":"46c7b24e-5b3f-4eb1-bc5a-20f6a0336cfe","uuid":"a2ef27ae-2086-42a4-9aa1-9ad1de4fbd05","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:49:19.441Z"}
