 story)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"ae0578874d9a509e3","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story created. Here is the summary:\n\n**Story file:** `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration.md`\n\n**Status:** Changed from `backlog` to `in-progress`.\n\n**4 ACs** with verification tags:\n- AC1-AC4: All tagged `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` -- these are all testable via unit tests mocking `detectStacks()` and verifying per-stack calls to `getCoverageTool()` / `instrumentProject()`, state output, and info messages.\n\n**11 Tasks** covering:\n- `getStackLabel()` multi-stack formatting (Task 1)\n- Per-stack info messages (Task 2)\n- Per-stack coverage detection loop (Task 3)\n- Per-stack OTLP instrumentation loop (Task 4)\n- State verification (Task 5)\n- 5 test tasks (Tasks 6-10)\n- Full regression run (Task 11)\n\n**3 files to change:** `init-project.ts`, `docs-scaffold.ts`, `init-project.test.ts`\n\n**Technical notes updated** to reflect the actual current code state after story 9-2 (which already added `detectStacks` import and basic stacks population), pinpointing exactly what remains single-stack (L75, L123, L138).\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Stale technical notes in original story:** The original story referenced line numbers from before story 9-2 was implemented (e.g., \"Replace at L68\" for `detectStack()` call). Story 9-2 already added `detectStacks()` at L70 and `stacks` population at L125. I rewrote the technical notes to reflect the actual current code state.\n- **`getStackLabel()` not in original Files to Change:** The original story listed `src/commands/init.ts` as needing changes but missed `docs-scaffold.ts`. After inspecting the code, `init.ts` does NOT reference `stack` from `InitResult` in a way that needs changing, but `getStackLabel()` in `docs-scaffold.ts` needs to accept arrays. Corrected the files list.\n- **Risk: `path` import missing in init-project.ts.** The per-stack OTLP loop needs `path.join()` for subdirectory resolution, but `init-project.ts` currently only imports `basename` from `node:path`. The dev will need to add `join` to the import.\n- **Observation:** Story 9-2's implementation already did partial work for this story (added `detectStacks` call and stacks population in state), reducing the scope. The remaining work is purely the per-stack iteration loops for coverage and OTLP, plus the multi-stack info message."}],"totalDurationMs":95678,"totalTokens":35011,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2054,"cache_read_input_tokens":32288,"output_tokens":668,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2054},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
