{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Aox8dXY5Wi267BR4SixXbk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→title: 'Enhanced Dev Story Definition of Done Checklist'\n     3→validation-target: 'Story markdown ({{story_path}})'\n     4→validation-criticality: 'HIGHEST'\n     5→required-inputs:\n     6→  - 'Story markdown file with enhanced Dev Notes containing comprehensive implementation context'\n     7→  - 'Completed Tasks/Subtasks section with all items marked [x]'\n     8→  - 'Updated File List section with all changed files'\n     9→  - 'Updated Dev Agent Record with implementation notes'\n    10→optional-inputs:\n    11→  - 'Test results output'\n    12→  - 'CI logs'\n    13→  - 'Linting reports'\n    14→validation-rules:\n    15→  - 'Only permitted story sections modified: Tasks/Subtasks checkboxes, Dev Agent Record, File List, Change Log, Status'\n    16→  - 'All implementation requirements from story Dev Notes must be satisfied'\n    17→  - 'Definition of Done checklist must pass completely'\n    18→  - 'Enhanced story context must contain sufficient technical guidance'\n    19→---\n    20→\n    21→# 🎯 Enhanced Definition of Done Checklist\n    22→\n    23→**Critical validation:** Story is truly ready for review only when ALL items below are satisfied\n    24→\n    25→## 📋 Context & Requirements Validation\n    26→\n    27→- [ ] **Story Context Completeness:** Dev Notes contains ALL necessary technical requirements, architecture patterns, and implementation guidance\n    28→- [ ] **Architecture Compliance:** Implementation follows all architectural requirements specified in Dev Notes\n    29→- [ ] **Technical Specifications:** All technical specifications (libraries, frameworks, versions) from Dev Notes are implemented correctly\n    30→- [ ] **Previous Story Learnings:** Previous story insights incorporated (if applicable) and build upon appropriately\n    31→\n    32→## ✅ Implementation Completion\n    33→\n    34→- [ ] **All Tasks Complete:** Every task and subtask marked complete with [x]\n    35→- [ ] **Acceptance Criteria Satisfaction:** Implementation satisfies EVERY Acceptance Criterion in the story\n    36→- [ ] **No Ambiguous Implementation:** Clear, unambiguous implementation that meets story requirements\n    37→- [ ] **Edge Cases Handled:** Error conditions and edge cases appropriately addressed\n    38→- [ ] **Dependencies Within Scope:** Only uses dependencies specified in story or project-context.md\n    39→\n    40→## 🧪 Testing & Quality Assurance\n    41→\n    42→- [ ] **Unit Tests:** Unit tests added/updated for ALL core functionality introduced/changed by this story\n    43→- [ ] **Integration Tests:** Integration tests added/updated for component interactions when story requirements demand them\n    44→- [ ] **End-to-End Tests:** End-to-end tests created for critical user flows when story requirements specify them\n    45→- [ ] **Test Coverage:** Tests cover acceptance criteria and edge cases from story Dev Notes\n    46→- [ ] **Regression Prevention:** ALL existing tests pass (no regressions introduced)\n    47→- [ ] **Code Quality:** Linting and static checks pass when configured in project\n    48→- [ ] **Test Framework Compliance:** Tests use project's testing frameworks and patterns from Dev Notes\n    49→\n    50→## 📝 Documentation & Tracking\n    51→\n    52→- [ ] **File List Complete:** File List includes EVERY new, modified, or deleted file (paths relative to repo root)\n    53→- [ ] **Dev Agent Record Updated:** Contains relevant Implementation Notes and/or Debug Log for this work\n    54→- [ ] **Change Log Updated:** Change Log includes clear summary of what changed and why\n    55→- [ ] **Review Follow-ups:** All review follow-up tasks (marked [AI-Review]) completed and corresponding review items marked resolved (if applicable)\n    56→- [ ] **Story Structure Compliance:** Only permitted sections of story file were modified\n    57→\n    58→## 🔚 Final Status Verification\n    59→\n    60→- [ ] **Story Status Updated:** Story Status set to \"review\"\n    61→- [ ] **Sprint Status Updated:** Sprint status updated to \"review\" (when sprint tracking is used)\n    62→- [ ] **Quality Gates Passed:** All quality checks and validations completed successfully\n    63→- [ ] **No HALT Conditions:** No blocking issues or incomplete work remaining\n    64→- [ ] **User Communication Ready:** Implementation summary prepared for user review\n    65→\n    66→## 🎯 Final Validation Output\n    67→\n    68→```\n    69→Definition of Done: {{PASS/FAIL}}\n    70→\n    71→✅ **Story Ready for Review:** {{story_key}}\n    72→📊 **Completion Score:** {{completed_items}}/{{total_items}} items passed\n    73→🔍 **Quality Gates:** {{quality_gates_status}}\n    74→📋 **Test Results:** {{test_results_summary}}\n    75→📝 **Documentation:** {{documentation_status}}\n    76→```\n    77→\n    78→**If FAIL:** List specific failures and required actions before story can be marked Ready for Review\n    79→\n    80→**If PASS:** Story is fully ready for code review and production consideration\n    81→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01GahX8iUoYR49K5t7MjQw49","session_id":"46c7b24e-5b3f-4eb1-bc5a-20f6a0336cfe","uuid":"57f2c140-585d-476d-b01a-588ea7be571f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:51:07.628Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gx9zQnGdZbNLNL6NSQ57iM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<workflow>\n     2→  <critical>The workflow execution engine is governed by: {project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/workflow.xml</critical>\n     3→  <critical>You MUST have already loaded and processed: {installed_path}/workflow.yaml</critical>\n     4→  <critical>Communicate all responses in {communication_language} and language MUST be tailored to {user_skill_level}</critical>\n     5→  <critical>Generate all documents in {document_output_language}</critical>\n     6→  <critical>Only modify the story file in these areas: Tasks/Subtasks checkboxes, Dev Agent Record (Debug Log, Completion Notes), File List,\n     7→    Change Log, and Status</critical>\n     8→  <critical>Execute ALL steps in exact order; do NOT skip steps</critical>\n     9→  <critical>Absolutely DO NOT stop because of \"milestones\", \"significant progress\", or \"session boundaries\". Continue in a single execution\n    10→    until the story is COMPLETE (all ACs satisfied and all tasks/subtasks checked) UNLESS a HALT condition is triggered or the USER gives\n    11→    other instruction.</critical>\n    12→  <critical>Do NOT schedule a \"next session\" or request review pauses unless a HALT condition applies. Only Step 6 decides completion.</critical>\n    13→  <critical>User skill level ({user_skill_level}) affects conversation style ONLY, not code updates.</critical>\n    14→\n    15→  <step n=\"1\" goal=\"Find next ready story and load it\" tag=\"sprint-status\">\n    16→    <check if=\"{{story_path}} is provided\">\n    17→      <action>Use {{story_path}} directly</action>\n    18→      <action>Read COMPLETE story file</action>\n    19→      <action>Extract story_key from filename or metadata</action>\n    20→      <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n    21→    </check>\n    22→\n    23→    <!-- Sprint-based story discovery -->\n    24→    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file exists\">\n    25→      <critical>MUST read COMPLETE sprint-status.yaml file from start to end to preserve order</critical>\n    26→      <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n    27→      <action>Read ALL lines from beginning to end - do not skip any content</action>\n    28→      <action>Parse the development_status section completely to understand story order</action>\n    29→\n    30→      <action>Find the FIRST story (by reading in order from top to bottom) where:\n    31→        - Key matches pattern: number-number-name (e.g., \"1-2-user-auth\")\n    32→        - NOT an epic key (epic-X) or retrospective (epic-X-retrospective)\n    33→        - Status value equals \"ready-for-dev\"\n    34→      </action>\n    35→\n    36→      <check if=\"no ready-for-dev or in-progress story found\">\n    37→        <output>📋 No ready-for-dev stories found in sprint-status.yaml\n    38→\n    39→          **Current Sprint Status:** {{sprint_status_summary}}\n    40→\n    41→          **What would you like to do?**\n    42→          1. Run `create-story` to create next story from epics with comprehensive context\n    43→          2. Run `*validate-create-story` to improve existing stories before development (recommended quality check)\n    44→          3. Specify a particular story file to develop (provide full path)\n    45→          4. Check {{sprint_status}} file to see current sprint status\n    46→\n    47→          💡 **Tip:** Stories in `ready-for-dev` may not have been validated. Consider running `validate-create-story` first for a quality\n    48→          check.\n    49→        </output>\n    50→        <ask>Choose option [1], [2], [3], or [4], or specify story file path:</ask>\n    51→\n    52→        <check if=\"user chooses '1'\">\n    53→          <action>HALT - Run create-story to create next story</action>\n    54→        </check>\n    55→\n    56→        <check if=\"user chooses '2'\">\n    57→          <action>HALT - Run validate-create-story to improve existing stories</action>\n    58→        </check>\n    59→\n    60→        <check if=\"user chooses '3'\">\n    61→          <ask>Provide the story file path to develop:</ask>\n    62→          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n    63→          <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n    64→        </check>\n    65→\n    66→        <check if=\"user chooses '4'\">\n    67→          <output>Loading {{sprint_status}} for detailed status review...</output>\n    68→          <action>Display detailed sprint status analysis</action>\n    69→          <action>HALT - User can review sprint status and provide story path</action>\n    70→        </check>\n    71→\n    72→        <check if=\"user provides story file path\">\n    73→          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n    74→          <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n    75→        </check>\n    76→      </check>\n    77→    </check>\n    78→\n    79→    <!-- Non-sprint story discovery -->\n    80→    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file does NOT exist\">\n    81→      <action>Search {implementation_artifacts} for stories directly</action>\n    82→      <action>Find stories with \"ready-for-dev\" status in files</action>\n    83→      <action>Look for story files matching pattern: *-*-*.md</action>\n    84→      <action>Read each candidate story file to check Status section</action>\n    85→\n    86→      <check if=\"no ready-for-dev stories found in story files\">\n    87→        <output>📋 No ready-for-dev stories found\n    88→\n    89→          **Available Options:**\n    90→          1. Run `create-story` to create next story from epics with comprehensive context\n    91→          2. Run `*validate-create-story` to improve existing stories\n    92→          3. Specify which story to develop\n    93→        </output>\n    94→        <ask>What would you like to do? Choose option [1], [2], or [3]:</ask>\n    95→\n    96→        <check if=\"user chooses '1'\">\n    97→          <action>HALT - Run create-story to create next story</action>\n    98→        </check>\n    99→\n   100→        <check if=\"user chooses '2'\">\n   101→          <action>HALT - Run validate-create-story to improve existing stories</action>\n   102→        </check>\n   103→\n   104→        <check if=\"user chooses '3'\">\n   105→          <ask>It's unclear what story you want developed. Please provide the full path to the story file:</ask>\n   106→          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n   107→          <action>Continue with provided story file</action>\n   108→        </check>\n   109→      </check>\n   110→\n   111→      <check if=\"ready-for-dev story found in files\">\n   112→        <action>Use discovered story file and extract story_key</action>\n   113→      </check>\n   114→    </check>\n   115→\n   116→    <action>Store the found story_key (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication\") for later status updates</action>\n   117→    <action>Find matching story file in {implementation_artifacts} using story_key pattern: {{story_key}}.md</action>\n   118→    <action>Read COMPLETE story file from discovered path</action>\n   119→\n   120→    <anchor id=\"task_check\" />\n   121→\n   122→    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Notes, Dev Agent Record, File List, Change Log, Status</action>\n   123→\n   124→    <action>Load comprehensive context from story file's Dev Notes section</action>\n   125→    <action>Extract developer guidance from Dev Notes: architecture requirements, previous learnings, technical specifications</action>\n   126→    <action>Use enhanced story context to inform implementation decisions and approaches</action>\n   127→\n   128→    <action>Identify first incomplete task (unchecked [ ]) in Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n   129→\n   130→    <action if=\"no incomplete tasks\">\n   131→      <goto step=\"6\">Completion sequence</goto>\n   132→    </action>\n   133→    <action if=\"story file inaccessible\">HALT: \"Cannot develop story without access to story file\"</action>\n   134→    <action if=\"incomplete task or subtask requirements ambiguous\">ASK user to clarify or HALT</action>\n   135→  </step>\n   136→\n   137→  <step n=\"2\" goal=\"Load project context and story information\">\n   138→    <critical>Load all available context to inform implementation</critical>\n   139→\n   140→    <action>Load {project_context} for coding standards and project-wide patterns (if exists)</action>\n   141→    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Notes, Dev Agent Record, File List, Change Log, Status</action>\n   142→    <action>Load comprehensive context from story file's Dev Notes section</action>\n   143→    <action>Extract developer guidance from Dev Notes: architecture requirements, previous learnings, technical specifications</action>\n   144→    <action>Use enhanced story context to inform implementation decisions and approaches</action>\n   145→    <output>✅ **Context Loaded**\n   146→      Story and project context available for implementation\n   147→    </output>\n   148→  </step>\n   149→\n   150→  <step n=\"3\" goal=\"Detect review continuation and extract review context\">\n   151→    <critical>Determine if this is a fresh start or continuation after code review</critical>\n   152→\n   153→    <action>Check if \"Senior Developer Review (AI)\" section exists in the story file</action>\n   154→    <action>Check if \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection exists under Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n   155→\n   156→    <check if=\"Senior Developer Review section exists\">\n   157→      <action>Set review_continuation = true</action>\n   158→      <action>Extract from \"Senior Developer Review (AI)\" section:\n   159→        - Review outcome (Approve/Changes Requested/Blocked)\n   160→        - Review date\n   161→        - Total action items with checkboxes (count checked vs unchecked)\n   162→        - Severity breakdown (High/Med/Low counts)\n   163→      </action>\n   164→      <action>Count unchecked [ ] review follow-up tasks in \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection</action>\n   165→      <action>Store list of unchecked review items as {{pending_review_items}}</action>\n   166→\n   167→      <output>⏯️ **Resuming Story After Code Review** ({{review_date}})\n   168→\n   169→        **Review Outcome:** {{review_outcome}}\n   170→        **Action Items:** {{unchecked_review_count}} remaining to address\n   171→        **Priorities:** {{high_count}} High, {{med_count}} Medium, {{low_count}} Low\n   172→\n   173→        **Strategy:** Will prioritize review follow-up tasks (marked [AI-Review]) before continuing with regular tasks.\n   174→      </output>\n   175→    </check>\n   176→\n   177→    <check if=\"Senior Developer Review section does NOT exist\">\n   178→      <action>Set review_continuation = false</action>\n   179→      <action>Set {{pending_review_items}} = empty</action>\n   180→\n   181→      <output>🚀 **Starting Fresh Implementation**\n   182→\n   183→        Story: {{story_key}}\n   184→        Story Status: {{current_status}}\n   185→        First incomplete task: {{first_task_description}}\n   186→      </output>\n   187→    </check>\n   188→  </step>\n   189→\n   190→  <step n=\"4\" goal=\"Mark story in-progress\" tag=\"sprint-status\">\n   191→    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file exists\">\n   192→      <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n   193→      <action>Read all development_status entries to find {{story_key}}</action>\n   194→      <action>Get current status value for development_status[{{story_key}}]</action>\n   195→\n   196→      <check if=\"current status == 'ready-for-dev' OR review_continuation == true\">\n   197→        <action>Update the story in the sprint status report to = \"in-progress\"</action>\n   198→        <output>🚀 Starting work on story {{story_key}}\n   199→          Status updated: ready-for-dev → in-progress\n   200→        </output>\n   201→      </check>\n   202→\n   203→      <check if=\"current status == 'in-progress'\">\n   204→        <output>⏯️ Resuming work on story {{story_key}}\n   205→          Story is already marked in-progress\n   206→        </output>\n   207→      </check>\n   208→\n   209→      <check if=\"current status is neither ready-for-dev nor in-progress\">\n   210→        <output>⚠️ Unexpected story status: {{current_status}}\n   211→          Expected ready-for-dev or in-progress. Continuing anyway...\n   212→        </output>\n   213→      </check>\n   214→\n   215→      <action>Store {{current_sprint_status}} for later use</action>\n   216→    </check>\n   217→\n   218→    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file does NOT exist\">\n   219→      <output>ℹ️ No sprint status file exists - story progress will be tracked in story file only</output>\n   220→      <action>Set {{current_sprint_status}} = \"no-sprint-tracking\"</action>\n   221→    </check>\n   222→  </step>\n   223→\n   224→  <step n=\"5\" goal=\"Implement task following red-green-refactor cycle\">\n   225→    <critical>FOLLOW THE STORY FILE TASKS/SUBTASKS SEQUENCE EXACTLY AS WRITTEN - NO DEVIATION</critical>\n   226→\n   227→    <action>Review the current task/subtask from the story file - this is your authoritative implementation guide</action>\n   228→    <action>Plan implementation following red-green-refactor cycle</action>\n   229→\n   230→    <!-- RED PHASE -->\n   231→    <action>Write FAILING tests first for the task/subtask functionality</action>\n   232→    <action>Confirm tests fail before implementation - this validates test correctness</action>\n   233→\n   234→    <!-- GREEN PHASE -->\n   235→    <action>Implement MINIMAL code to make tests pass</action>\n   236→    <action>Run tests to confirm they now pass</action>\n   237→    <action>Handle error conditions and edge cases as specified in task/subtask</action>\n   238→\n   239→    <!-- REFACTOR PHASE -->\n   240→    <action>Improve code structure while keeping tests green</action>\n   241→    <action>Ensure code follows architecture patterns and coding standards from Dev Notes</action>\n   242→\n   243→    <action>Document technical approach and decisions in Dev Agent Record → Implementation Plan</action>\n   244→\n   245→    <action if=\"new dependencies required beyond story specifications\">HALT: \"Additional dependencies need user approval\"</action>\n   246→    <action if=\"3 consecutive implementation failures occur\">HALT and request guidance</action>\n   247→    <action if=\"required configuration is missing\">HALT: \"Cannot proceed without necessary configuration files\"</action>\n   248→\n   249→    <critical>NEVER implement anything not mapped to a specific task/subtask in the story file</critical>\n   250→    <critical>NEVER proceed to next task until current task/subtask is complete AND tests pass</critical>\n   251→    <critical>Execute continuously without pausing until all tasks/subtasks are complete or explicit HALT condition</critical>\n   252→    <critical>Do NOT propose to pause for review until Step 9 completion gates are satisfied</critical>\n   253→  </step>\n   254→\n   255→  <!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:dev-enforcement -->\n   256→  <step n=\"5.5\" goal=\"Harness enforcement gates\">\n   257→    <critical>Codeharness requires these checks before proceeding to tests</critical>\n   258→    <action>Verify AGENTS.md files are updated for all modules touched during implementation</action>\n   259→    <action>Create or update exec-plan in docs/exec-plans/active/ for this story</action>\n   260→    <action>Ensure all new code has appropriate test stubs before writing full tests</action>\n   261→    <action>Run `codeharness coverage` to execute tests with coverage and set session flags (tests_passed, coverage_met)</action>\n   262→    <action>If codeharness coverage is not installed or fails, fall back to running test suite manually and verify 100% coverage target</action>\n   263→    <action if=\"tests_passed is false\">HALT: \"Tests failed — fix tests before continuing\"</action>\n   264→    <action if=\"coverage_met is false\">HALT: \"Coverage target not met — add tests before continuing\"</action>\n   265→  </step>\n   266→  <!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:dev-enforcement -->\n   267→\n   268→  <step n=\"6\" goal=\"Author comprehensive tests\">\n   269→    <action>Create unit tests for business logic and core functionality introduced/changed by the task</action>\n   270→    <action>Add integration tests for component interactions specified in story requirements</action>\n   271→    <action>Include end-to-end tests for critical user flows when story requirements demand them</action>\n   272→    <action>Cover edge cases and error handling scenarios identified in story Dev Notes</action>\n   273→  </step>\n   274→\n   275→  <step n=\"7\" goal=\"Run validations and tests\">\n   276→    <action>Determine how to run tests for this repo (infer test framework from project structure)</action>\n   277→    <action>Run all existing tests to ensure no regressions</action>\n   278→    <action>Run the new tests to verify implementation correctness</action>\n   279→    <action>Run linting and code quality checks if configured in project</action>\n   280→    <action>Validate implementation meets ALL story acceptance criteria; enforce quantitative thresholds explicitly</action>\n   281→    <action if=\"regression tests fail\">STOP and fix before continuing - identify breaking changes immediately</action>\n   282→    <action if=\"new tests fail\">STOP and fix before continuing - ensure implementation correctness</action>\n   283→  </step>\n   284→\n   285→  <step n=\"8\" goal=\"Validate and mark task complete ONLY when fully done\">\n   286→    <critical>NEVER mark a task complete unless ALL conditions are met - NO LYING OR CHEATING</critical>\n   287→\n   288→    <!-- VALIDATION GATES -->\n   289→    <action>Verify ALL tests for this task/subtask ACTUALLY EXIST and PASS 100%</action>\n   290→    <action>Confirm implementation matches EXACTLY what the task/subtask specifies - no extra features</action>\n   291→    <action>Validate that ALL acceptance criteria related to this task are satisfied</action>\n   292→    <action>Run full test suite to ensure NO regressions introduced</action>\n   293→\n   294→    <!-- REVIEW FOLLOW-UP HANDLING -->\n   295→    <check if=\"task is review follow-up (has [AI-Review] prefix)\">\n   296→      <action>Extract review item details (severity, description, related AC/file)</action>\n   297→      <action>Add to resolution tracking list: {{resolved_review_items}}</action>\n   298→\n   299→      <!-- Mark task in Review Follow-ups section -->\n   300→      <action>Mark task checkbox [x] in \"Tasks/Subtasks → Review Follow-ups (AI)\" section</action>\n   301→\n   302→      <!-- CRITICAL: Also mark corresponding action item in review section -->\n   303→      <action>Find matching action item in \"Senior Developer Review (AI) → Action Items\" section by matching description</action>\n   304→      <action>Mark that action item checkbox [x] as resolved</action>\n   305→\n   306→      <action>Add to Dev Agent Record → Completion Notes: \"✅ Resolved review finding [{{severity}}]: {{description}}\"</action>\n   307→    </check>\n   308→\n   309→    <!-- ONLY MARK COMPLETE IF ALL VALIDATION PASS -->\n   310→    <check if=\"ALL validation gates pass AND tests ACTUALLY exist and pass\">\n   311→      <action>ONLY THEN mark the task (and subtasks) checkbox with [x]</action>\n   312→      <action>Update File List section with ALL new, modified, or deleted files (paths relative to repo root)</action>\n   313→      <action>Add completion notes to Dev Agent Record summarizing what was ACTUALLY implemented and tested</action>\n   314→    </check>\n   315→\n   316→    <check if=\"ANY validation fails\">\n   317→      <action>DO NOT mark task complete - fix issues first</action>\n   318→      <action>HALT if unable to fix validation failures</action>\n   319→    </check>\n   320→\n   321→    <check if=\"review_continuation == true and {{resolved_review_items}} is not empty\">\n   322→      <action>Count total resolved review items in this session</action>\n   323→      <action>Add Change Log entry: \"Addressed code review findings - {{resolved_count}} items resolved (Date: {{date}})\"</action>\n   324→    </check>\n   325→\n   326→    <action>Save the story file</action>\n   327→    <action>Determine if more incomplete tasks remain</action>\n   328→    <action if=\"more tasks remain\">\n   329→      <goto step=\"5\">Next task</goto>\n   330→    </action>\n   331→    <action if=\"no tasks remain\">\n   332→      <goto step=\"9\">Completion</goto>\n   333→    </action>\n   334→  </step>\n   335→\n   336→  <step n=\"9\" goal=\"Story completion and mark for review\" tag=\"sprint-status\">\n   337→    <action>Verify ALL tasks and subtasks are marked [x] (re-scan the story document now)</action>\n   338→    <action>Run the full regression suite (do not skip)</action>\n   339→    <action>Confirm File List includes every changed file</action>\n   340→    <action>Execute enhanced definition-of-done validation</action>\n   341→    <action>Update the story Status to: \"review\"</action>\n   342→\n   343→    <!-- Enhanced Definition of Done Validation -->\n   344→    <action>Validate definition-of-done checklist with essential requirements:\n   345→      - All tasks/subtasks marked complete with [x]\n   346→      - Implementation satisfies every Acceptance Criterion\n   347→      - Unit tests for core functionality added/updated\n   348→      - Integration tests for component interactions added when required\n   349→      - End-to-end tests for critical flows added when story demands them\n   350→      - All tests pass (no regressions, new tests successful)\n   351→      - Code quality checks pass (linting, static analysis if configured)\n   352→      - File List includes every new/modified/deleted file (relative paths)\n   353→      - Dev Agent Record contains implementation notes\n   354→      - Change Log includes summary of changes\n   355→      - Only permitted story sections were modified\n   356→    </action>\n   357→\n   358→    <!-- Mark story ready for review - sprint status conditional -->\n   359→    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file exists AND {{current_sprint_status}} != 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n   360→      <action>Load the FULL file: {sprint_status}</action>\n   361→      <action>Find development_status key matching {{story_key}}</action>\n   362→      <action>Verify current status is \"in-progress\" (expected previous state)</action>\n   363→      <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"review\"</action>\n   364→      <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure including STATUS DEFINITIONS</action>\n   365→      <output>✅ Story status updated to \"review\" in sprint-status.yaml</output>\n   366→    </check>\n   367→\n   368→    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file does NOT exist OR {{current_sprint_status}} == 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n   369→      <output>ℹ️ Story status updated to \"review\" in story file (no sprint tracking configured)</output>\n   370→    </check>\n   371→\n   372→    <check if=\"story key not found in sprint status\">\n   373→      <output>⚠️ Story file updated, but sprint-status update failed: {{story_key}} not found\n   374→\n   375→        Story status is set to \"review\" in file, but sprint-status.yaml may be out of sync.\n   376→      </output>\n   377→    </check>\n   378→\n   379→    <!-- Final validation gates -->\n   380→    <action if=\"any task is incomplete\">HALT - Complete remaining tasks before marking ready for review</action>\n   381→    <action if=\"regression failures exist\">HALT - Fix regression issues before completing</action>\n   382→    <action if=\"File List is incomplete\">HALT - Update File List with all changed files</action>\n   383→    <action if=\"definition-of-done validation fails\">HALT - Address DoD failures before completing</action>\n   384→  </step>\n   385→\n   386→  <step n=\"10\" goal=\"Completion communication and user support\">\n   387→    <action>Execute the enhanced definition-of-done checklist using the validation framework</action>\n   388→    <action>Prepare a concise summary in Dev Agent Record → Completion Notes</action>\n   389→\n   390→    <action>Communicate to {user_name} that story implementation is complete and ready for review</action>\n   391→    <action>Summarize key accomplishments: story ID, story key, title, key changes made, tests added, files modified</action>\n   392→    <action>Provide the story file path and current status (now \"review\")</action>\n   393→\n   394→    <action>Based on {user_skill_level}, ask if user needs any explanations about:\n   395→      - What was implemented and how it works\n   396→      - Why certain technical decisions were made\n   397→      - How to test or verify the changes\n   398→      - Any patterns, libraries, or approaches used\n   399→      - Anything else they'd like clarified\n   400→    </action>\n   401→\n   402→    <check if=\"user asks for explanations\">\n   403→      <action>Provide clear, contextual explanations tailored to {user_skill_level}</action>\n   404→      <action>Use examples and references to specific code when helpful</action>\n   405→    </check>\n   406→\n   407→    <action>Once explanations are complete (or user indicates no questions), suggest logical next steps</action>\n   408→    <action>Recommended next steps (flexible based on project setup):\n   409→      - Review the implemented story and test the changes\n   410→      - Verify all acceptance criteria are met\n   411→      - Ensure deployment readiness if applicable\n   412→      - Run `code-review` workflow for peer review\n   413→      - Optional: If Test Architect module installed, run `/bmad:tea:automate` to expand