{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016ypbYL3F6ndHJATjxdYhUM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 9-3: Init orchestrator per-stack iteration\n     2→\n     3→## Status: review\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer running `codeharness init` on a multi-stack project,\n     8→I want coverage and OTLP to be configured for each detected stack,\n     9→So that all languages get observability and test coverage.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [x] AC1: Given a multi-stack project (nodejs + rust), when `codeharness init` runs, then coverage tools are detected for each stack independently (c8 for nodejs, cargo-tarpaulin for rust) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [x] AC2: Given a multi-stack project (nodejs + rust), when `codeharness init` runs, then OTLP packages are installed for each stack independently (npm packages for nodejs, cargo crates for rust) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [x] AC3: Given a multi-stack project, when `codeharness init` runs, then info messages list all detected stacks (e.g., `Stack detected: Node.js (package.json) + Rust (Cargo.toml)`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [x] AC4: Given a multi-stack project, when state is created, then `state.stacks` contains all detected stack names and `state.app_type` reflects primary stack <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→\n    18→## Tasks/Subtasks\n    19→\n    20→- [x] Task 1: Update `getStackLabel()` in `docs-scaffold.ts` to accept `string | string[]` and format multi-stack output (e.g., `Node.js (package.json) + Rust (Cargo.toml)`)\n    21→- [x] Task 2: In `init-project.ts` L75, change info message to pass `result.stacks` (or all stack names) to `getStackLabel()` so multi-stack projects show all stacks\n    22→- [x] Task 3: In `init-project.ts` L123, replace single `getCoverageTool(stack)` with per-stack loop over `allStacks`, calling `getCoverageTool()` per stack and storing results (primary stack's tool in `state.coverage.tool` for backward compat)\n    23→- [x] Task 4: In `init-project.ts` L138, replace single `instrumentProject(projectDir, stack, ...)` with per-stack loop over `allStacks`, calling `instrumentProject()` per detection with correct subdirectory path\n    24→- [x] Task 5: Verify `state.stacks` is persisted correctly (already done in story 9-2 at L125 — confirm no changes needed)\n    25→- [x] Task 6: Add test — multi-stack init calls `getCoverageTool()` once per detected stack\n    26→- [x] Task 7: Add test — multi-stack init calls `instrumentProject()` once per detected stack with correct dir\n    27→- [x] Task 8: Add test — info output includes all detected stacks label\n    28→- [x] Task 9: Add test — state file after multi-stack init has `stacks: ['nodejs', 'rust']` and `app_type` set from primary stack\n    29→- [x] Task 10: Add test — single-stack backward compat: single-stack project still works identically\n    30→- [x] Task 11: Run full test suite — verify zero regressions\n    31→\n    32→## Dev Agent Record\n    33→\n    34→### Implementation Plan\n    35→\n    36→- Updated `getStackLabel()` to accept `string | string[] | null` with array support via recursive mapping and `+` join\n    37→- Changed info message to use `result.stacks` array when populated, falling back to single stack\n    38→- Added per-stack coverage detection loop over `allStacks`, keeping primary stack's tool in `state.coverage.tool`\n    39→- Replaced single `instrumentProject()` with per-stack loop using correct subdirectory paths\n    40→- Added `join` import from `node:path` for subdirectory path construction\n    41→- Confirmed `state.stacks` persistence from story 9-2 is intact\n    42→\n    43→### Debug Log\n    44→\n    45→No issues encountered during implementation.\n    46→\n    47→### Completion Notes\n    48→\n    49→All 11 tasks implemented and verified. 5 new multi-stack tests added to init-project.test.ts, 3 new getStackLabel array tests added to docs-scaffold.test.ts. Full test suite: 3105 tests pass across 114 files with zero regressions.\n    50→\n    51→## File List\n    52→\n    53→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — Per-stack coverage and OTLP loops, multi-stack info message, added `join` import\n    54→- `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — `getStackLabel()` now accepts `string | string[] | null`\n    55→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts` — 5 new multi-stack orchestration tests, added mocks for detectStacks/getCoverageTool/instrumentProject\n    56→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` — 3 new getStackLabel array tests\n    57→\n    58→## Change Log\n    59→\n    60→- 2026-03-23: Implemented per-stack iteration for coverage detection and OTLP instrumentation in init orchestrator. Updated getStackLabel for multi-stack display. Added 8 new tests.\n    61→\n    62→## Technical Notes\n    63→\n    64→### Current state after story 9-2\n    65→\n    66→Story 9-2 already added `detectStacks` import and basic `stacks` population in `init-project.ts`:\n    67→- L9: `import { detectStack, detectStacks, detectAppType } from '../../lib/stack-detect.js';`\n    68→- L70-71: `const allStacks = detectStacks(projectDir);` and `result.stacks = [...new Set(allStacks.map(s => s.stack))];`\n    69→- L125: `state.stacks = result.stacks as import('../../lib/stack-detect.js').StackName[];`\n    70→\n    71→What is NOT yet multi-stack:\n    72→- L75: `info(\\`Stack detected: ${getStackLabel(stack)}\\`)` — uses single stack, not all stacks\n    73→- L123: `state.coverage.tool = getCoverageTool(stack);` — single stack coverage only\n    74→- L138: `result.otlp = instrumentProject(projectDir, stack, { json: isJson, appType });` — single stack OTLP only\n    75→\n    76→### Changes to `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts`\n    77→\n    78→**Info message (L74-77):** Replace `getStackLabel(stack)` with `getStackLabel(result.stacks)` (after updating `getStackLabel` to accept arrays). Show all stacks in the detection message.\n    79→\n    80→**Per-stack coverage (L123):** Replace single `getCoverageTool(stack)` with iteration over `allStacks`. For each detection, compute the coverage tool. Store primary stack's tool in `state.coverage.tool` for backward compat. Optionally store a `state.coverage.tools` map for future consumers.\n    81→\n    82→**Per-stack OTLP (L134-139):** Replace single `instrumentProject()` call with loop:\n    83→```ts\n    84→for (const detection of allStacks) {\n    85→  const stackDir = detection.dir === '.' ? projectDir : path.join(projectDir, detection.dir);\n    86→  const stackOtlp = instrumentProject(stackDir, detection.stack, { json: isJson, appType });\n    87→  // Collect results; primary stack's result goes to result.otlp for backward compat\n    88→}\n    89→```\n    90→\n    91→### Important: coverage.ts and otlp.ts internals do NOT change\n    92→\n    93→`getCoverageTool()` and `instrumentProject()` keep their single-stack signatures. The orchestrator loops — the internals don't know about multi-stack. This is the minimal API surface change strategy from the tech spec.\n    94→\n    95→### `getStackLabel()` in docs-scaffold.ts\n    96→\n    97→Currently accepts `string | null`. Needs to also accept `string[]` to format multi-stack labels. When given an array, join with ` + ` separator. The stack-to-label mapping (nodejs -> `Node.js (package.json)`, rust -> `Rust (Cargo.toml)`, python -> `Python`) already exists.\n    98→\n    99→### Test file\n   100→\n   101→Update `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts`:\n   102→- Mock `detectStacks()` to return multi-stack result `[{ stack: 'nodejs', dir: '.' }, { stack: 'rust', dir: '.' }]`\n   103→- Verify `getCoverageTool()` called once per stack\n   104→- Verify `instrumentProject()` called once per stack with correct dir\n   105→- Verify state has `stacks: ['nodejs', 'rust']`\n   106→- Verify single-stack still works (backward compat)\n   107→\n   108→## Files to Change\n   109→\n   110→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — Add per-stack iteration loops for coverage detection and OTLP instrumentation, update info message to show all stacks\n   111→- `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Update `getStackLabel()` to accept `string | string[]` for multi-stack label formatting\n   112→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts` — Add multi-stack orchestration tests (per-stack coverage, per-stack OTLP, state fields, info messages, backward compat)\n   113→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RW3DvRwuMditE8CiVokyWA","session_id":"46c7b24e-5b3f-4eb1-bc5a-20f6a0336cfe","uuid":"0d4d57ef-2b7b-47e8-82ef-9cec952d8655","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:55:56.750Z"}
