{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WL9B3KoEh38SPzGyZsqvtQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 7)\n     2→\n     3→### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — create-story (2026-03-23T14:24Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Ambiguity:** Epic says `stacks: string[]` but `StackName` union type exists from story 9-1. Chose `StackName[]` for type safety.\n     6→- **Missing context:** `InitResult` in `types.ts` may need `stacks` field but epic FR4 doesn't explicitly call it out — implied by scope.\n     7→- **Risk:** `detectStacks()` can return duplicate stack names from multiple directories. `stacks` field needs deduplication.\n     8→- **Observation:** All 8 ACs are cli-verifiable via unit tests — no external dependencies.\n     9→\n    10→### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:32Z)\n    11→\n    12→- **Pre-existing type errors:** `bridge.test.ts` implicit `any`, `run.test.ts` spread arg type error, `stack.test.ts` missing `endpoint`, `status.test.ts` missing `timeoutSummary`. None from this story.\n    13→- **Workaround:** Used `stacks: ['nodejs'] as StackName[]` instead of `as const` in `stack.test.ts` because readonly tuples aren't assignable to `StackName[]`.\n    14→- **Risk:** `recoverCorruptedState()` recovery path not directly unit-tested for `stacks` field — would need planted `package.json` in temp dir.\n    15→- **Observation:** 19 new tests added, all 3098 tests pass with 0 failures.\n    16→\n    17→### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — code-review (2026-03-23T14:36Z)\n    18→\n    19→- **HIGH (fixed):** `init-project.ts` never persisted multi-stacks to state file — only single root stack written. All `detectStacks()` results lost on init.\n    20→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `writeState()` mutated caller's state object via `state.stack = state.stacks[0]` side effect.\n    21→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `isValidState()` accepted `stacks: [42, true]` as valid — no element type checking.\n    22→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` produced inconsistent `stack: null` / `stacks: ['nodejs']` state.\n    23→- **LOW (not fixed):** `migrateState()` casts `raw.stack as StackName` without validating against known stack names.\n    24→- **LOW (not fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` calls both `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()` — detection runs twice.\n    25→- **LOW (not fixed):** Flaky test in `sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts > writeStateAtomic` — shared file race condition under parallel execution.\n    26→- **Coverage gap:** `init-project.test.ts` has zero assertions on `stacks` field after init. No test for recovery when root null but subdirs have stacks.\n    27→\n    28→---\n    29→\n    30→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 8)\n    31→\n    32→### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — create-story (2026-03-23T14:50Z)\n    33→\n    34→- **Stale technical notes:** Original story referenced line numbers from before story 9-2. Rewrote to reflect actual current code state.\n    35→- **Files list correction:** Original story listed `src/commands/init.ts` but missed `docs-scaffold.ts`. `init.ts` doesn't need changes; `docs-scaffold.ts` does for `getStackLabel()`.\n    36→- **Risk:** `path` import missing in init-project.ts — per-stack OTLP loop needs `path.join()` but only `basename` is imported.\n    37→- **Observation:** Story 9-2 already did partial work (added `detectStacks` call and stacks population), reducing scope to per-stack iteration loops.\n    38→\n    39→### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:55Z)\n    40→\n    41→- **Code quality concern:** Per-stack coverage loop calls `getCoverageTool()` per stack but discards return value — `HarnessState.coverage` only has single `tool` field, not per-stack map. Future addition needed.\n    42→- **Observation:** OTLP per-stack loop assigns `result.otlp` based on matching `detection.stack === stack` (primary stack). Last match wins if duplicates exist.\n    43→- **Observation:** Fallback `if (!result.otlp)` after OTLP loop handles edge case where primary stack isn't in `allStacks`.\n    44→\n    45→### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — code-review (2026-03-23T15:02Z)\n    46→\n    47→- **HIGH (fixed):** Per-stack coverage loop was dead code — called `getCoverageTool()` per stack but discarded all return values\n    48→- **HIGH (fixed):** OTLP `result.otlp` matched by stack name only, wrong detection when multiple subdirs share same stack\n    49→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Double filesystem scan — `detectStack()` calls `detectStacks()` internally, then init called it again\n    50→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Integration tests mocked `detectStack` but init-project no longer called it after refactor\n    51→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `state.coverage.tools` assigned without type interface field existing\n    52→- **LOW (not fixed):** `state.coverage.tools` map persisted but no consumer reads it yet\n    53→- **LOW (not fixed):** `detectAppType` only considers primary root stack in multi-stack projects\n    54→\n    55→### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — verify (2026-03-23T15:08Z)\n    56→\n    57→- All 4 ACs passed black-box verification\n    58→- Beads sync failed (story file status line not found) — non-blocking\n    59→- Container cleanup succeeded\n    60→- Observability check: VictoriaMetrics stack was down at start, `codeharness stack start` reported shared stack already running (inconsistent)\n    61→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01QpfV7KAcFxhwb5m8bRBBca","session_id":"46c7b24e-5b3f-4eb1-bc5a-20f6a0336cfe","uuid":"5cb7123d-4d18-4d67-a2f0-041e4f8f8070","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:09:39.147Z"}
