{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012cbtKaey6KKFChjtNwYrpX","type":"tool_result","content":"  1680→# Session 7 Retrospective — 2026-03-23T14:21Z\n  1681→\n  1682→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint\n  1683→**Session window:** 14:21 - 14:51 UTC (~30 minutes)\n  1684→**Story attempted:** 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack\n  1685→**Final status:** verifying (black-box verification in progress when time expired)\n  1686→\n  1687→---\n  1688→\n  1689→## 1. Session Summary\n  1690→\n  1691→| Story | Start Status | End Status | Outcome |\n  1692→|-------|-------------|------------|---------|\n  1693→| 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack | backlog | verifying | Created, implemented, reviewed, verification started but not completed |\n  1694→\n  1695→Story 9-2 progressed through create → dev → code-review → verification start within 25 minutes. The black-box Docker verification was launched but did not complete before the time budget expired. The verifier process (`claude --print`) is still running and will need to be picked up or restarted by the next session.\n  1696→\n  1697→## 2. Issues Analysis\n  1698→\n  1699→### Bugs Found During Code Review (4 fixed)\n  1700→\n  1701→1. **HIGH — init-project.ts never persisted multi-stacks.** `detectStacks()` results were computed but never written to the state file during `codeharness init`. Only the single root stack from `getDefaultState(stack)` survived. This would have meant multi-stack detection was completely broken for new inits.\n  1702→\n  1703→2. **MEDIUM — writeState() mutated caller's state object.** The backward-compat sync (`state.stack = state.stacks[0]`) modified the input object as a side effect. Could cause subtle bugs if callers hold references to state objects.\n  1704→\n  1705→3. **MEDIUM — isValidState() accepted non-string stacks array.** `stacks: [42, true]` passed validation. Type safety gap.\n  1706→\n  1707→4. **MEDIUM — recoverCorruptedState() inconsistent state.** When root `detectStack()` returned null but subdirectory `detectStacks()` found stacks, the state had `stack: null` with `stacks: ['nodejs']`. The consistency relied on the writeState mutation bug (#2) to fix itself.\n  1708→\n  1709→### Unfixed Issues (LOW priority)\n  1710→\n  1711→- `migrateState()` casts `raw.stack as StackName` without validating — old state files with `stack: 'go'` would produce invalid `stacks: ['go']`\n  1712→- `recoverCorruptedState()` runs detection twice (calls both `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()`, latter internally calls the former)\n  1713→- Flaky test: `sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts > writeStateAtomic` — shared file race condition under parallel execution (pre-existing)\n  1714→\n  1715→### Coverage Gaps\n  1716→\n  1717→- `init-project.test.ts` has zero assertions on `stacks` field after init\n  1718→- No test for recovery when root stack is null but subdirectory stacks exist\n  1719→\n  1720→### Spec Ambiguities\n  1721→\n  1722→- Epic spec said `stacks: string[]` but `StackName` union type exists from story 9-1. Implementation used `StackName[]` for type safety — correct decision.\n  1723→- `InitResult.stacks` wasn't explicitly called out in FR4 but was implied by scope.\n  1724→\n  1725→### Infrastructure\n  1726→\n  1727→- Observability stack port conflict: `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to bind ports already used by shared stack containers. Resolved by using the shared stack directly.\n  1728→- Stale Docker container (`codeharness-verify`) left from previous session — had to force-remove before starting new one.\n  1729→\n  1730→## 3. What Went Well\n  1731→\n  1732→- **Create → dev → review pipeline executed smoothly.** Story went from backlog to verifying in ~20 minutes.\n  1733→- **Code review caught 4 real bugs** including a HIGH that would have made multi-stack init completely broken.\n  1734→- **3100 tests passing** with 19 new migration tests added. Zero regressions.\n  1735→- **97.03% coverage**, all 123 files above 80% floor.\n  1736→\n  1737→## 4. What Went Wrong\n  1738→\n  1739→- **Verification didn't complete in time.** The black-box verifier (claude --print) takes several minutes and was launched too late in the session.\n  1740→- **Time budget awareness was insufficient.** Should have started verification earlier or recognized that state migration ACs are better suited for unit-testable verification (all 8 ACs test internal functions).\n  1741→\n  1742→## 5. Lessons Learned\n  1743→\n  1744→- **State migration stories should be tagged `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->`.** ACs 1-7 test internal state functions that have zero external effects — they can't meaningfully be verified via CLI alone. AC8 (regression) just needs `npm test`. Black-box verification for this story type wastes time on infrastructure setup for no additional confidence.\n  1745→- **Start verification earlier.** If the story reaches `verifying` with >15 minutes remaining, verification has a good chance of completing. With <10 minutes, skip to retro.\n  1746→- **Clean up Docker containers proactively.** The stale container from the previous session wasted a minute on diagnosis.\n  1747→\n  1748→## 6. Action Items\n  1749→\n  1750→### Fix Now (before next session)\n  1751→- Next session should complete the verification for 9-2 (it's at `verifying` status)\n  1752→\n  1753→### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n  1754→- Add `stacks` assertions to `init-project.test.ts`\n  1755→- Add test for recovery when root stack null + subdirectory stacks present\n  1756→- Consider tagging pure-state stories as unit-testable to avoid Docker overhead\n  1757→\n  1758→### Backlog\n  1759→- Fix flaky `writeStateAtomic` test (shared file race condition)\n  1760→- Validate `StackName` enum values in `migrateState()` instead of blind cast\n  1761→- Optimize `recoverCorruptedState()` to avoid double detection\n  1762→\n  1763→## Session Metrics\n  1764→\n  1765→| Metric | Value |\n  1766→|--------|-------|\n  1767→| Stories attempted | 1 |\n  1768→| Stories completed | 0 (verification in progress) |\n  1769→| Stories failed | 0 |\n  1770→| Bugs found by review | 4 (1 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM) |\n  1771→| Tests added | 19 new + 2 from review = 21 |\n  1772→| Total tests passing | 3100 |\n  1773→| Coverage | 97.03% |\n  1774→| Sprint completion | 35/39 = ~90% (counting 9-2 as nearly done) |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01QpfV7KAcFxhwb5m8bRBBca","session_id":"46c7b24e-5b3f-4eb1-bc5a-20f6a0336cfe","uuid":"518467dd-ec83-42aa-9004-c49572070139","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:10:14.071Z"}
